stry studies perspective, an analysis of how the DVD market influenced the production of American horror films, and an examination of films from Splat Pack members such as Eli Roth, Rob Zombie, James Wan, and Alexandre Aja.By re-examining the history of the American horror film from a business perspective and exploring how DVD influenced the production of American horror films in the early twenty-first century, this thought-provoking book provides students and scholars in Film Studies with an alternative perspective on the Splat Pack."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aDVD-Video discsxMarketingxUnited States. 0aDVD-Video discszUnited States. 0aDVDs. 0aHorror filmsxEconomic aspectsxHistory. 0aHorror filmsxEconomic aspectszUnited States. 0aHorror filmsxHistory and criticismxUnited States. 0aHorror filmsxProduction and directionxUnited States. 0aHorror filmsxProduction and directionzUnited States. 0aHorror filmszUnited StatesxHistory and criticism. 0aHorror filmszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aMotion picture industryxUnited States. 0aMotion picture industryzUnited States. 0aSplatter filmsxEconomic aspectsxHistory. 0aSplatter filmsxHistory and criticismxUnited States. 0aSplatter filmsxProduction and directionxUnited States. 4aFilm, Media & Cultural Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / Direction & Production.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311078045140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780748685509?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780748685509423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780748685509/original  a978-3-11-078045-1  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  